history.content:
If would add a fourth class it should be a light breadth - the current schedule you have now is a decent and managable workload (especially if you're trying to recruit this fall). 

EE127 has weekly psets which can eat up some time in the middle of the week. 

Stat135 has biweekly psets, so you work on them on the weekends in between 127 psets. 

I haven't taken 186 myself but my friends who took it in the spring reported that the workload was definitely higher than other people had said it would be (and its a nice balance of coding to the two previous psets).
Should I consider adding a fourth lighter class or is this already a pretty busy workload?
history.subject: ee 127 + cs 186 + stat 135 workload?
